Our group project was based on Jenniffer & Co. Salon and Spa. We based it off the location on Mentor Ave. which is the biggest. We based our problem on Saturdays from 8 am-5pm which is the bussiest day. 

We seperated the salon into several areas, Hair and Makeup, The Spa, The Tanning area, and the Nail Area. Using the MMS Opt Template we analyzed each of the areas indivdually to determine the best number of servers based on the amount of customers coming in, the time it took to give a service, the cost of giving a service, and the number of technicians available. 

We did the problem to figure out how to best get people through a certain area in order to make room for new clients, to figure out if we were being as efficient as possible, to find if a certain area needed more marketing, and to find the best way to expand the nail area by taking out tanning beds.

By doing the problem we learned something different in each area analyzed. In the nail area we figured out how to best expand into the tanning area, by figuring out the best number of nail servers to have and how many tanning beds to remove to meet the highest demand in both areas. 

In the hair and makeup area we figured out the optimum number of stylists to have just in case a new client wanted to come in a server needed to be available. 

In the spa area, we figured out there needs to be more marketing of this area because due to the current amount of clients that come in during the busiest times, there is no need for the third room, so we need to get more clients coming in so that room in needed. For the current time period, it is best to have two spa people in that area and a third person the can serve as a floater and do spa services as well as hair in order to meet the deman while marketing slowly brings in more clients. Once marketing has brought in enough cliental a third permanent person will need to be in the spa area.
